Package stack

Class CalcStack

java.lang.Object
stack.CalcStack
public class CalcStack extends Object

stack.CalcStack - Custom stack created specifically for MyCalculator. The stack uses List instead of the standard Array[] to perform the basic operations of stack.

stack.CalcStack provides basic stack operations like push(String), pop(), peek(). Additionally, the user can also check whether the stack is Empty by using the isEmpty() method.

A constructor with no arguments is called to initialize the List and int that acts as a placeholder for the stack's TOP.

Author:
Harsh Indoria
